  "commentary": "With SPX at 6605.66 sitting just below the GEX flip at 6609 and massive positive gamma walls at 6605 (+74.8B) and 6610 (+99.1B), dealers are likely providing heavy selling pressure on any upside attempts while supporting dips back toward 6605. The recent wall break and GEX surge (67% in 5 minutes) suggests we just saw significant options flow that has dealers scrambling to hedge, creating the current PIN regime with strong mean reversion forces. Key levels: 6610 is the critical resistance where dealer selling intensifies, 6605 provides support, and any break below 6590 flips dealers from stabilizing to amplifying mode.\n\nBottom line: expect tight range-bound action between 6605-6610 with dealers capping moves in both directions.",
